```markdown
# ğŸ” Permissions & Ownership Commands â€“ Day 2

## Commands Used

```bash
ls -l
chmod 755 testfile.txt
chmod +x script.sh
chown root:root testfile.txt
sudo chown $USER:$USER testfile.txt
Notes
Understanding rwx is key for privilege escalation.

chmod +x makes a file executable.

Ownership controls who can access or modify files.

