# ğŸ” Day 2 â€“ Why Linux Skills Matter for Bug Bounty

Most bug bounty programs run Linux servers.

Understanding Linux helps you:
- Read server config files
- Understand web app deployment
- Analyze permissions issues
- Identify misconfigurations
- Recognize dangerous service settings
- Understand log files
- Exploit poorly configured cron jobs
- Detect insecure file permissions

Becoming comfortable in Linux = becoming dangerous as a hacker.
